Thousands of troops were deployed to Baluchistan after a rocket attack on a gas plant killed eight people.
Tribal rebels attacked a paramilitary convoy, resulting in three soldiers dead and seven injured.
The rebels claimed up to 50 casualties, but officials disputed the number.
Fierce gun battles between rebels and troops left 30 dead and 70 injured.
The violence escalated after a doctor was raped at the gas field.
Thousands fled their homes as clashes intensified, with a rebel chief warning of danger.
The situation remains tense as security forces brace for further conflict.
